nalysis of a range of food-centered arenas, Uncertain Tastes argues that the experience of food itself—symbolic, sensuous, social, and material-is intrinsically characterized by multiple and frequently conflicting layers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCulture conflictzKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood habitszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFood preferenceszKenyazSamburu District. 0aFoodxSymbolic aspectszKenyazSamburu District. 0aSamburu (African people)xDomestic animals. 0aSamburu (African people)xFood. 0aSamburu (African people)xSocial conditions. 0aSocial changezKenyazSamburu District. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094482440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944824/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles